{"ts": "2026-04-03T00:02:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "tighten-spec-template-and-plan-verification-requirements", "findings": ["The requirements alignment claim reads into project.md a preference for the template enforcement mechanism, but the requirements document is silent on whether enforcement belongs in templates, in a gate agent, in a reviewer hook, or nowhere structured — the claim goes beyond what the source supports.", "The scope boundedness claim asserts the evaluator agent is excluded, but the source material frames the evaluator as 'the cheaper alternative' (implying it was deselected on cost grounds, not formally excluded) — an implementer could reasonably read this as the evaluator remaining a valid option.", "The 'Gaps to close' section names categories of required additions but provides no stopping condition — the source does not define what a completed template looks like, meaning scope is bounded by category but open-ended in extent and format.", "The HIGH intent clarity rating absorbs the causal claim 'reduces overnight deferrals' as established fact, but the source provides no data on how many deferrals are caused by ambiguous specs or whether template changes would have prevented them."], "dispositions": {"apply": 1, "dismiss": 3, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Added research open question: determine the exact format and required section structure for the spec template and plan.md verification strategy, so the stopping condition is concrete."], "status": "ok"}
